  <summary>12/18/1987--Introduced.
Treaty Termination Procedure Act of 1987 - Prohibits the United States from exercising its right to terminate, withdraw from, or suspend the operation of any treaty or treaty provision to which it is a party unless specifically authorized to do so by an Act of the Congress.</summary>
